node.text:
What a project this has been. From sitting in a car park in Roth in 2016, spinning some ideas (thank goodness the beam bike never got the go ahead ; ) to getting comfortable with disc brakes, holding a first 3D print and seeing it all come together with some hard data in the wind tunnel. Thank you @canyon for keeping me close on this project and the ‘blood, sweat and tears’ you put into this bike – I promise to repay it on race day.

Two weeks ago today, Tri At Home went from ridiculous idea to unbelievable reality. A full Iron distance triathlon. All live streamed. All indoors. With an incredible array of guests prepared to give up their time to help me pass the time. All to raise money for some undeniably worthy causes. Thank you to all those who made it possible. Thank you to all those contributed prizes or donated. These are some of my highlights.

#frodissimo #stayathome #triathome #ironman #triathlon #challenge #unitedinhumanity
